edu.rit.numeric

Class Int96

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.numeric.Int96
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Int96>

    public class Int96
extends Object
implements Comparable<Int96>
    Class Int96 provides a fixed-size 96-bit signed integer.

    Int96 objects are mutable. Many of the methods alter the state of the Int96 object on which they are invoked. This avoids creation of unnecessary Int96 objects when performing a series of operations. However, if necessary, you must explicitly create a new Int96 object upon which to perform a series of operations.

    Class Int96 defines the equals() and hashCode() methods, so Int96 objects can be used as keys in hashed data structures. However, be careful not to alter the state of an Int96 object once it is used as a key. Also, never alter the state of the predefined ZERO, ONE, TWO, and TEN objects.

    Class Int96 is not multiple thread safe. However, each constructor and method only alters the Int96 object on which the constructor or method is called. The constructors and methods do not alter their arguments.
